There are tons of Korean takeout joints on Oahu but for a sit-down meal Sorabol has been my go-to for over 10 years now. Consistent quality of food, average but attentive service and outstanding spicy raw crab. My go-to dishes are (preferably, if available, on the lunch menu which is a bit cheaper than dinner): spicy raw crab, fish jun, kal bi, and crab jigae. Their menu is vast, like most Korean joints, but if you're tired of takeout and limited ban chan options, I highly suggest Sorabol.

This place has been around for decades and I think it has been several since I last visited. Unfortunate for me that I waited so long as they got really good food there that I have been missing out on.  Probably a big reason for not going sooner is the parking situation in the area.  Their parking lot can be challenging most of the time and the surrounding areas have very limited street parking.  Your best bet to secure parking and not deal with a headache of hunting for a spot is to just park across the street the Walmart.  Usually the second floor is wide open and you can so some shopping afterwards if you should so choose.  We ordered a bubbling joy of Crab Stew (Spicy) and Intestine Tripe Stew (mild) which both were excellent.  They arrived hot and fresh.  Flavors were just amazing and portion sizes large.  My only complaint on the Crab Stew, but they provided no tools for cracking the crab parts or extra napkins as you have to dig in and get down and dirty with this stew, but it was worth it as there was lots of crab.  Another great part about the meal was the excellent banchan.  I think this is a real deciding factor for me when it comes to Korean restaurants on how much effort they put into their banchan.  The staff are all very friendly and attentive.  It was comfortable and clean. Definitely will go back and do recommend it to others.
